 simulations, the presence of a low\nionization region near the disk mid-plane, which we call the ambipolar damping\nzone, results in reduced stresses there.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2013 20:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Aug 2013 21:53:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
