 and crossing of the mutual 1:2 MMR of Jupiter and Saturn are unlikely\nto provide suitable orbital conditions for the formation of solar system\nterrestrial planets. This suggests that to explain Mars' small mass and the\nabsence of other planets between Mars and Jupiter, the outer asteroid belt must\nhave suffered a severe depletion due to interactions with Jupiter/Saturn, or by\nan alternative mechanism (e.g., rogue super-Earths).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Jun 2013 03:40:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 28 Jun 2013 03:25:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-08-05"}
